compareVersionStrings

public static int compareVersionStrings(String left,
                                        String right)
Compare two versions strings with each other by splitting at the . and comparing the integer values. Additional string like "-update1" are ignored, i.e. "2.2" is considered equal to "2.2-update1".

Parameters:
left - A version string, e.g. "2.1".
right - A version string, e.g. "4.2.2".
Returns:
0 if the versions are equal. 1 if the left side is bigger. -1 if the right side is bigger.
